'''''The Pipes of Pan''''' (French: '''''La flûte de Pan''''') is an [[oil-on-canvas]] by Spanish artist [[Pablo Picasso]]. Painted in 1923 during Picasso's [[Pablo Picasso#Classicism and surrealism|classical period]], the painting depicts two statuesque men of mythological origins.

